description.plain:
Dreamwastaken (b. August 12, 1999), or simply Dream, is a content creator most known for his Minecraft content on both YouTube and Twitch.  He was born and raised in Orlando, Florida.

In 2021, he announced his debut single “Roadtrip” featuring PmBata. After the release of the song, he mentioned on Twitter he would like to experiment with multiple types of music, as he has said that he is continuously seeking to try new things for the experience.

All of his music can be found on the Dream Music YouTube channel and on all music streaming platforms. Like Dream’s other channels, Dream Music saw an increase in subscribers within minutes because of “Roadtrip” being released.

songs.full_title: Mask by Dream
songs.title: Mask

description.plain:
On “Mask,” Dream reflects about his past fights with mental disorders like depression and ADHD while acknowledging how they affect him in his current life. The song’s title plays with the lyrics as a shield, hiding Dream’s insecurities while he fights these mental illnesses. He confirmed the title on March 14 when replying to a fan via his defunct private Twitter account, dreamhangout.

The day before, Dream first teased his fans that confirmed he was working on a new song via said Twitter account.

“Mask” aims for a rock beat while maintaining classic pop elements from Dream’s collaboration with producers Banrisk and Perish Beats called “Roadtrip.” Following the immense success of this February 2021 hit, “Mask” is the second collaboration between the three artists.

The song is also Dream’s second song Twitter user @camruna designed cover art for. They had previously designed the cover art for “Roadtrip” under a different name, @acaicamc.

songs.full_title: Bye L’manberg by Dream
songs.title: Bye L’manberg

description.plain:
“Bye L'Manberg” is about the aftermath of the Doomsday War on the Minecraft roleplay server, the Dream SMP. The song is Dream’s reaction to the end of the war, which happened when he successfully blew up the fictional country of L'Manburg with the help of his friends Technoblade and Ph1LzA and permanently disbanding it.

Dream slightly changed the lyrics from Wilbur Soot’s L'Manberg national anthem to show how happy Dream is about L'Manberg being gone.
